<subSubSection id="05C98A0C6E3E871DBAFC92E8AD4D531A" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="7A4875BB5A057D231C8D626240517435" pageId="17" pageNumber="130">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD921EB456A67394A56C65B71DDC11FA" pageId="17" pageNumber="130">
This group contains at least 19 described species (
<bibRefCitation id="B3AC13ED70CC8CA59B2905A82522E6C7" author="Toledano, L" journalOrPublisher="Koleopterologische Rundschau" pageId="27" pageNumber="140" pagination="1 - 14" title="Nomenclatorial revision of the supraspecific taxa of Bembidiini s. str. of South America described by Jeannel (1962) and related taxa with some descriptions of the fauna of South America (Coleoptera: Carabidae)." volume="72" year="2002">Toledano 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EC658D65E20FCB0F63E451A4BCBE5A4F" author="Toledano, L" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Biodiversity" pageId="27" pageNumber="140" pagination="81 - 130" title="Systematic notes on the Bembidiina of the northern Andes with particular reference to the fauna of Ecuador (Coleoptera, Carabidae)." volume="1" year="2008">Toledano 2008</bibRefCitation>
), and is characterized by males having an aedeagus lacking a brush sclerite, and with a very long flagellum (
<bibRefCitation id="50EE32BE7DC0B761B09D92A7EDD42DE4" author="Maddison, DR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="27" pageNumber="140" pagination="547 - 560" title="Phylogenetic relationships of the South American ground beetle subgenus Chilioperyphus Jeannel (Coleoptera: Carabidae: Trechinae: Bembidiini: Bembidion Latreille)." url="10.11646/zootaxa.3636.4.3" volume="3636" year="2013">Maddison et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="9824F9A82BAD466D20BB9C73D7B2F843" author="Toledano, L" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Biodiversity" pageId="27" pageNumber="140" pagination="81 - 130" title="Systematic notes on the Bembidiina of the northern Andes with particular reference to the fauna of Ecuador (Coleoptera, Carabidae)." volume="1" year="2008">Toledano 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4695B925D5D16DC313C91A1880DA7E00" pageId="17" pageNumber="130">
Included here are some species previously placed in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="FF2D4E986E0313459E6052D74A893380" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphus</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="A9A771B7F09044CBD74C24528BAE758B" author="Jeannel, R" editor="Deboutteville, CD" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="26" pageNumber="139" pagination="527 - 655" title="Les Trechides de la Paleantarctide occidentale." volumeTitle="Biologie de l'Amerique Australe, Etudes sur la Faune du Sol" year="1962">Jeannel (1962)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName id="43A2943F88CEE4E0F1E22F121852456B" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion hirtipes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtipes">Bembidion hirtipes</taxonomicName>
(Jeannel), 
<taxonomicName id="71786A893C9F398CDA897265BA7B95AB" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion ringueleti" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ringueleti">Bembidion ringueleti</taxonomicName>
(Jeannel), 
<taxonomicName id="23BAF9EDC3EE0A374A7BD48AE180745B" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion rufoplagiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoplagiatum">Bembidion rufoplagiatum</taxonomicName>
Germain, 
<taxonomicName id="E67049FF711839A087B354350CCA9FF7" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion uniforme" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uniforme">Bembidion uniforme</taxonomicName>
Csiki, and 
<taxonomicName id="AF0215954F5108E6461AE066B71753D4" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion parvum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvum">Bembidion parvum</taxonomicName>
(Jeannel). 
<taxonomicName id="3DD818AFDBF870A65ED81393C725592F" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidium mandibulare" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibulare">Bembidium mandibulare</taxonomicName>
Solier belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="68AED825FFDE3D2C52ED4F27CAD7A9C3" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
as well, and is nested well within it (Fig. 8); thus, subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="E2A000362D88DABBCDE9F45681C930FA" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Plocamoperyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plocamoperyphus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Plocamoperyphus</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="56E0B6E1C95CFEE39DEBB7437C6078B3" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
. There are no morphological characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="EB2D7F1540C99BF3D5C54978D4484E99" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidium mandibulare" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibulare">Bembidium mandibulare</taxonomicName>
that would suggest it is not a member of 
<taxonomicName id="7EF289BB755ECB790E5FD8BB4365AF0E" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
; it shares all apomorphies of the group. As first reviser, I choose 
<taxonomicName id="3C22918960DB9CD6FC441F2C1E3C82AB" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
as the valid name of the group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4EC29EB1172DF4EACE6E01BDF6CEFB52" pageId="17" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicName id="D8294F638B6AEBD40B3EF9FCECE99DDB" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
has two distinct clades, each very well supported: the 
<taxonomicName id="72F78222BCB355BDE0A8C834F0E7454B" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion caoduroi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caoduroi">Bembidion caoduroi</taxonomicName>
group (clade j in Fig. 8; Fig. 1D), consisting (among the sampled species) of three large species from the northern Andes (Fig. 1D); (2) the remaining 
<taxonomicName id="DCBC7EEA301663C61C982ADF7DEAACA6" genus="Antiperypanes" lsidName="Antiperypanes" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" rank="genus">Antiperypanes</taxonomicName>
(clade k in Fig. 8; Figs 1
<normalizedToken id="0BBE9AA74CA5D3ABA3F12CA3F8380294" originalValue="A–C">A-C</normalizedToken>
, E). Each is supported by MLB=100 and PB=100 in the multi-gene analyses, and individually by support from five to seven genes (Table 3). As a whole, however, the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="9A52FC2EDC6189FB428A986B90864C51" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
is only weakly supported by the combined analysis and analyses of four genes (Table 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ABF29CAAECDF1764734E3857DEDE980C" pageId="17" pageNumber="130">
Members of this subgenus are found at the edges of bodies of water. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="A5F3C308001D2D281C0F98A0973AEA7D" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion rufoplagiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoplagiatum">Bembidion rufoplagiatum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C347D857C78C01C0A17BDC872A0DAB4E" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion zanettii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zanettii">Bembidion zanettii</taxonomicName>
are common on gravel and cobble river shores, 
<taxonomicName id="C6A562592D2B9D417C3561A4E4707CE5" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion ringueleti" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ringueleti">Bembidion ringueleti</taxonomicName>
is found on gravel and sand shores of smaller creeks, and 
<taxonomicName id="BF6886A364187BBE7B64185260147EA8" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidium mandibulare" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibulare">Bembidium mandibulare</taxonomicName>
on the sand beaches of the Pacific Ocean in Chile and sand beaches of rivers in Argentina.
</paragraph>
